## [T1] Source download tracking

Per-URL retry and block-detection state. Updated by the lead after each download subagent reports in. `Attempts` is incremented on each dispatch. Sources with `Attempts ≥ 3` that are still failing are auto-flagged without user prompt.

| Canonical URL | Attempts | Last Failure Reason | File Size (bytes) | Local Path | Status |
| :------------ | :------- | :------------------ | :---------------- | :--------- | :----- |
| `<<url>>` | `0` | `—` | `—` | `—` | `pending` |

**Status values:**
- `pending` — not yet dispatched to a subagent
- `downloaded` — `fetch_url` succeeded; file on disk
- `uploaded` — `ragflow_upload` succeeded; `doc_id` recorded
- `rate-limited` — file suspiciously small; Cloudflare or server throttle detected; awaiting user retry decision
- `pending-retry` — user approved retry; subagent re-dispatched
- `access-denied` — HTTP 403 / access-denied content detected; permanently excluded
- `auto-flagged-invalid` — attempted ≥ 3 times; automatically excluded
- `excluded` — dropped to `sources_excluded.md` (any reason)

